WEBVTT	#Elemental Media Engine(TM) 2.17.0.0

00:00:00.00 --> 00:00:02.91
We are joined now by the State Department's Undersecretary

00:00:02.91 --> 00:00:04.83
for Political Affairs, Victoria Nuland.

00:00:04.83 --> 00:00:07.98
She was also ambassador to NATO under the second Bush

00:00:07.98 --> 00:00:08.68
administration.

00:00:08.68 --> 00:00:11.22
So she knows this subject area very well.

00:00:11.22 --> 00:00:13.75
Ambassador Nuland, thank you for joining us.

00:00:13.75 --> 00:00:16.41
I want to get to that first question about the direction

00:00:16.41 --> 00:00:18.00
of the crisis.

00:00:18.00 --> 00:00:20.73
Is it escalating or de-escalating?

00:00:20.73 --> 00:00:23.22
What's the latest?

00:00:23.22 --> 00:00:24.87
Tony, even though President Putin

00:00:24.87 --> 00:00:27.36
is claiming he's withdrawing, our concern

00:00:27.36 --> 00:00:30.24
is that the troops that matter, those that are ringing Ukraine

00:00:30.24 --> 00:00:33.09
to the north, to the east, and to the south

00:00:33.09 --> 00:00:35.67
are actually increasing their readiness.

00:00:35.67 --> 00:00:37.98
So he is maintaining every option

00:00:37.98 --> 00:00:40.68
to go in at a time of his choosing.

00:00:40.68 --> 00:00:42.52
So it sounds like from your perspective,

00:00:42.52 --> 00:00:45.51
we're still in a crisis or escalation phase of this,

00:00:45.51 --> 00:00:47.04
not de-escalation.

00:00:47.04 --> 00:00:51.54
There was a cyber attack on the Ukrainian army and two banks

00:00:51.54 --> 00:00:52.74
in the country yesterday.

00:00:52.74 --> 00:00:54.45
Is it the belief of the US government

00:00:54.45 --> 00:00:58.29
that that was Putin laying the groundwork potentially

00:00:58.29 --> 00:01:00.51
for a broader assault?

00:01:00.51 --> 00:01:03.00
Well, we're still investigating and doing

00:01:03.00 --> 00:01:05.13
forensics, along with the Ukrainians.

00:01:05.13 --> 00:01:07.80
I think what's most important is that these cyber attacks were

00:01:07.80 --> 00:01:10.08
not very successful.

00:01:10.08 --> 00:01:11.88
Both the Ministry of Defense and the banks

00:01:11.88 --> 00:01:14.61
were able to reestablish in real time.

00:01:14.61 --> 00:01:16.74
And that is a direct result of the hard work

00:01:16.74 --> 00:01:19.20
that the Ukrainians have been doing with our help

00:01:19.20 --> 00:01:20.73
to make themselves resilient.

00:01:20.73 --> 00:01:22.35
But who is best at this?

00:01:22.35 --> 00:01:24.30
Who uses this weapon all around the world?

00:01:24.30 --> 00:01:26.57
Obviously, the Kremlin.

00:01:26.57 --> 00:01:28.32
Ambassador, we cover this story every day.

00:01:28.32 --> 00:01:29.77
We have for weeks now.

00:01:29.77 --> 00:01:31.50
But for the average Americans sitting

00:01:31.50 --> 00:01:35.43
at home who wants to understand why this former Soviet Republic

00:01:35.43 --> 00:01:37.23
halfway around the world seems to be

00:01:37.23 --> 00:01:40.08
so important to the current administration, what do

00:01:40.08 --> 00:01:42.00
you say to them?

00:01:42.00 --> 00:01:46.77
What I say to them is if an authoritarian leader anywhere

00:01:46.77 --> 00:01:50.07
in the world is able to invade their neighbor

00:01:50.07 --> 00:01:53.82
and take them over by force and deny them sovereignty,

00:01:53.82 --> 00:01:56.07
then this won't end at Ukraine.

00:01:56.07 --> 00:01:58.42
It'll happen all around the world.

00:01:58.42 --> 00:02:00.54
China is watching vis-a-vis Taiwan.

00:02:00.54 --> 00:02:01.62
Iran is watching.

00:02:01.62 --> 00:02:03.24
North Korea is watching.

00:02:03.24 --> 00:02:08.01
So we have to maintain UN principles of international law

00:02:08.01 --> 00:02:10.20
that protect the sovereignty and territorial

00:02:10.20 --> 00:02:12.51
integrity of every single country,

00:02:12.51 --> 00:02:14.59
notably including Ukraine.

00:02:14.59 --> 00:02:17.31
That is the front line of the democracies

00:02:17.31 --> 00:02:20.94
versus the autocracies competition at this moment.

00:02:20.94 --> 00:02:25.08
Ambassador, President Putin's goal here,

00:02:25.08 --> 00:02:27.03
to the best we can understand it,

00:02:27.03 --> 00:02:29.52
is to limit the encroachment of NATO

00:02:29.52 --> 00:02:34.47
on Russia's border, so the eastern expansion of NATO.

00:02:34.47 --> 00:02:38.22
Why is it so important for NATO to continue

00:02:38.22 --> 00:02:39.96
to move in that direction?

00:02:39.96 --> 00:02:44.22
And is it your concern that Putin could take Ukraine today,

00:02:44.22 --> 00:02:47.10
but then move to rebuild, essentially, the former Soviet

00:02:47.10 --> 00:02:49.83
Union in the future?

00:02:49.83 --> 00:02:52.53
Tony, NATO is a defensive alliance.

00:02:52.53 --> 00:02:55.71
Its purpose since its founding in 1949

00:02:55.71 --> 00:02:58.90
is to protect the security of its members.

00:02:58.90 --> 00:03:02.34
So if you are not coming for us, we are not coming for you.

00:03:02.34 --> 00:03:06.03
And, in fact, NATO never even had any forces

00:03:06.03 --> 00:03:09.33
on its eastern edge, in Poland or the Baltic states,

00:03:09.33 --> 00:03:14.05
until after Russia took Crimea and invaded Eastern Ukraine.

00:03:14.05 --> 00:03:21.11
So this is a conflict of Russia's own making.

00:03:21.11 --> 00:03:24.11
Ambassador, I know that the US government does not

00:03:24.11 --> 00:03:26.33
want to detail what the sanctions will

00:03:26.33 --> 00:03:29.21
be against Putin and Russia if there is an invasion.

00:03:29.21 --> 00:03:31.22
However, I am curious to know why

00:03:31.22 --> 00:03:33.86
you are confident sanctions will work

00:03:33.86 --> 00:03:36.56
or could work in this scenario, given they have not been

00:03:36.56 --> 00:03:38.36
successful in prior conflicts.

00:03:38.36 --> 00:03:41.18
I'm thinking of Crimea.

00:03:41.18 --> 00:03:44.57
Tony, what we are preparing this time with the European Union

00:03:44.57 --> 00:03:47.45
and other allies and partners around the world, including

00:03:47.45 --> 00:03:52.04
the UK and Canada, will be absolutely crushing financially

00:03:52.04 --> 00:03:55.88
for Russia and in terms of Russia's ability

00:03:55.88 --> 00:03:59.87
to grow its economy and modernize going forward.

00:03:59.87 --> 00:04:03.71
So not only will this be a bloody awful conflict

00:04:03.71 --> 00:04:06.23
for Ukraine and for the Russian people,

00:04:06.23 --> 00:04:09.71
it will also throw Russia back into isolation

00:04:09.71 --> 00:04:11.60
for a very, very long time.

00:04:11.60 --> 00:04:15.09
You asked me a question about rebuilding the Soviet Union.

00:04:15.09 --> 00:04:20.81
This is the concern, that Putin has a revanchist fantasy

00:04:20.81 --> 00:04:23.87
about rebuilding the former Soviet Union,

00:04:23.87 --> 00:04:27.02
whether it starts with Ukraine, it includes Belarus.

00:04:27.02 --> 00:04:28.88
It could go as far as Moldova.

00:04:28.88 --> 00:04:31.88
And that will throw not only Europe, but the world

00:04:31.88 --> 00:04:33.83
back into a Cold War posture.

00:04:33.83 --> 00:04:35.93
And that's what we're trying to prevent.

00:04:35.93 --> 00:04:39.75
And that's why we want to see diplomacy succeed here

00:04:39.75 --> 00:04:41.72
and why we're continuing to press that

00:04:41.72 --> 00:04:45.05
with Putin and with everybody else on the Russian side.

00:04:45.05 --> 00:04:47.99
And to avoid, as you put it, a "bloody, awful conflict."

00:04:47.99 --> 00:04:49.75
Ambassador Nuland, thank you.

00:04:49.75 --> 00:04:50.42
Thank you, Tony.

00:04:50.42 --> 00:04:52.06
All right.